  "Hakan Koç and cofounder Christian Bertermann founded Berlin-based used car marketplace Auto1 in 2012 and took it public in early 2021. \r\n",
  "Auto1 bought over 600,000 used cars in 2019; it sells vehicles to dealerships and drivers directly, with cars delivered in glass-fronted trucks. ",
  "Koç stepped down as co-CEO in November 2020 to take up a role on the company's supervisory board",
  "Koç started with Berlin's startup factory Rocket Internet in 2010 before working at online home goods website Home24 as chief product officer.",
  "Koç attended Germany's elite Bucerius Law School. He grew up in Kiel, Germany, the son of Turkish immigrants."
